events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Stephen Garcia threw three touchdown passes and Marcus Lattimore had two clinching TD runs as No. 19 South Carolina stunned No. 1 Alabama 35-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Carolina topples No. 1 Bama

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Terrelle Pryor threw for a career-best 334 yards and three touchdowns to lead No. 2 Ohio State past surprisingly punchless Indiana 38-10 on Saturday, giving coach Jim Tressel his 100th victory on the Buckeyes sideline.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pryor powers Ohio St.

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: LaMichael James scored three touchdowns, including an 84-yard scoring reception, and No. 3 Oregon shook Washington State in the second half for a 43-23 win on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ducks survive

events.name: Toledo Rockets at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Jeremy Avery ran for three touchdowns, Kellen Moore passed for three more and the defense forced four turnovers to lift No. 4 Boise State to an easy 57-14 victory over Toledo Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise St. fires on all cylinders

events.name: Wyoming Cowboys at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Andy Dalton threw for a season-high 270 yards and three touchdowns a week after his worst game of the season and TCU recorded consecutive shutouts for the first time in 55 years in the No. 5 Frogs' 45-0 victory against Wyoming.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU blasts Wyoming

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Cam Newton drove Auburn into position for Wes Byrum's 24-yard field goal as time expired, lifting the eighth-ranked Tigers past Kentucky 37-34 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 8 Auburn clips UK as time expires

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Ryan Katz threw for 393 yards and two touchdowns, sneaked across for another score and Oregon State held on to upset No. 9 Arizona 29-27 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Katz leads Oregon St. past No. 9 Zona

events.name: Utah Utes at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Jordan Wynn threw for 325 yards and two touchdowns, Shaky Smithson threw a TD pass and caught another one and No. 10 Utah blew past host Iowa State 68-27
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 10 Utah erupts

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Ryan Mallett threw three touchdown passes in the first half then struggled to do anything else, and safety Tramain Thomas intercepted a pass in the end zone on the game's final play to give No. 11 Arkansas a 24-17 victory over Texas A&M.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late pick preserves Arkansas victory

events.name: LSU Tigers at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jarrett Lee tossed a 3-yard touchdown pass to Terrence Tolliver with 6 seconds left after LSU kept its final drive alive with a successful fake field goal, and the 12th-ranked Tigers pulled out another wild win, 33-29 against No. 14 Florida on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: LSU ekes out wild win over Florida

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Jermaine Thomas scored a career-high three touchdowns, Chris Thompson rushed for 158 yards and No. 23 Florida State ran out to a huge lead on the way to beating No. 13 Miami 45-17 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas, Florida St. run through Miami

events.name: USC Trojans at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Nate Whitaker made up for a missed extra point by kicking a 30-yard field goal on the final play to give No. 16 Stanford a 37-35 victory over Southern California on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Whitaker lifts Stanford past USC on final play

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: With coach Mark Dantonio back in the stadium, No. 17 Michigan State took advantage of three interceptions by Denard Robinson and scored 24 unanswered points to break open a close game and beat No. 17 Michigan 34-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spartans stall Robinson, Wolverines

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: John Clay ran for three touchdowns and freshman James White added two more to lead No. 20 Wisconsin to a 41-23 win over Minnesota on Saturday to keep Paul Bunyan's Axe for the seventh straight year.
headlines.shortLinkText: 3 Clay TDs help Wisconsin control Minnesota

events.name: San Jose State Spartans at Nevada Wolf Pack

headlines.description: Vai Taua ran for 196 yards and three touchdowns and Colin Kaepernick passed for 273 yards, rushed for 91 and scored twice Saturday night to keep No. 21 Nevada undefeated with a 35-13 win over San Jose State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Taua too much for San Jose St. as Nevada rolls

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Blaine Gabbert threw two touchdown passes before leaving with a hip pointer after three quarters and No. 24 Missouri got several big plays on special teams along with stout defense in a 26-0 victory over Colorado in a Big 12 opener on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gabbert hurts hip but keeps Missouri unbeaten

events.name: Colorado State Rams at Air Force Falcons

headlines.description: No. 25 Air Force added some air to the nation's top-ranked running attack and Jonathan Warzeka returned a kickoff 100 yards for a touchdown in a 49-27 rout of Colorado State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Air Force celebrates ranking with big victory

events.name: Syracuse Orange at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: Delone Carter rushed for 105 yards and Ryan Nassib finished a 98-yard scoring drive with a touchdown pass to Marcus Sales, helping Syracuse win its Big East opener Saturday with a 13-9 victory over South Florida.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cuse tops USF, wins Big East opener

events.name: Boston College Eagles at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Russell Wilson threw for 328 yards and three touchdowns to help North Carolina State beat Boston College 44-17 on Saturday, giving Tom O'Brien his first win against his former program.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson's 328 yards help NC State dominate BC

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Mikel Leshoure ran for 119 yards, Nate Bussey had a 16-yard interception return for a score Saturday and Illinois pounded injury-depleted Penn State in a 33-13 win to spoil homecoming in Happy Valley.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illinois' D dominant

events.name: Central Michigan Chippewas at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Quarterback Tyrod Taylor rushed for 127 yards and two touchdowns and threw for another score to lead Virginia Tech past Central Michigan 45-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Virginia Tech drops CMU to earn 4th straight win

events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Ball State Cardinals

headlines.description: W. Michigan 45, Ball St. 16
headlines.shortLinkText: W. Michigan 45, Ball St. 16

events.name: Temple Owls at Northern Illinois Huskies

headlines.description: Chandler Harnish threw two touchdown passes and Chad Spann rushed for 100 yards and a score as Northern Illinois beat Temple 31-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Two Harnish TD passes lift NIU past Temple

events.name: Baylor Bears at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Taylor Potts threw for 462 yards and four touchdowns, and Texas Tech avoided its first-ever 0-3 start in the Big 12 as it held off Baylor 45-38 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas Tech gets Big 12 win behind Potts' 4 TDs

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray ran for two touchdowns and threw for two more scores as Georgia snapped a four-game losing streak, routing bumbling Tennessee 41-14 Saturday in a rude homecoming for Volunteers coach Derek Dooley.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia snaps skid by trampling Tennessee

Memphis Tigers at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Adam Froman threw four first-half touchdown passes and Bilal Powell rushed for 204 yards with two scores to lead Louisville to a 56-0 win over Memphis on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Led by QB Froman, Louisville lashes Memphis

events.name: UCLA Bruins at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Shane Vereen rushed for 151 yards and two touchdowns, Marvin Jones  scored on a 48-yard reverse and California's defense limited UCLA to 144 yards of offense in the Golden Bears' 35-7 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cal D dominant; Vereen, Bears run over UCLA

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Anthony Allen ran for 195 yards and three touchdowns and Georgia Tech posted its best rushing total in an Atlantic Coast Conference game to beat Virginia 33-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen, Georgia Tech run wild against Virginia

events.name: Pittsburgh Panthers at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Dayne Crist ran for a TD and passed for another and David Ruffer stayed perfect on field goals by kicking three more Saturday as Notre Dame held on to beat Pittsburgh 23-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Field goals help Notre Dame edge Pitt

events.name: Clemson Tigers at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Johnny White rushed for two touchdowns and gained 179 total yards, and North Carolina held on to beat Clemson 21-16 on Saturday for its third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: White carries depleted UNC over Clemson

events.name: UNLV Rebels at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw three touchdown passes to Brad Starks, Noel Devine rushed for two scores and quick-strike West Virginia beat UNLV 49-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith, Devine help West Virginia run over UNLV

Navy Midshipmen at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Ricky Dobbs led a brilliant touchdown drive capped by a 6-yard pass to Greg Jones with 26 seconds left to give Navy a 28-27 win and hand Wake Forest its second straight last-minute loss.

headlines.description: Quarterback Larry Smith threw for 253 yards and two touchdowns and ran for another as Vanderbilt rolled to a 52-6 victory over Eastern Michigan on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vandy's 2nd quarter powers rout of E. Michigan

events.name: Arkansas State Red Wolves at North Texas Mean Green

headlines.description: Ryan Aplin  rushed for two touchdowns and passed for another to lead Arkansas State to a 24-19 victory against North Texas on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aplin's 3 TDs lift Arkansas St. over North Texas

events.name: Miami (OH) RedHawks at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Zach Collaros threw three touchdown passes -- two of them long strikes to Armon Binns -- and Isaiah Pead had a pair of long runs during Cincinnati's big first half Saturday night, sending the Bearcats to a 45-3 victory over local rival Miami of Ohio.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collaros tosses 3 TDs as Cincinnati wins big
